<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd" []>
<task xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="inserting-external-xref-to-existing-document" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:task.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Inserting External Xref to an Existing Document</title>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p id="insert-external-xref-to-existing-document-intro">You can insert an external  xref pointing to a target in another document that already exists.</p>
      <p>Do the following:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step id="step-call-insert-external-xref-dialog">
        <cmd>Call up the <uicontrol>Insert External Xref Dialog</uicontrol>. </cmd>
        <info>
          <p>To call up the <keyword>Insert External Xref Dialog</keyword>, choose <menucascade>
              <uicontrol>DITA</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Insert External Xref</uicontrol>
            </menucascade> or click the <uicontrol>Insert External Xref</uicontrol> button <image href="insert-external-xreference-button.png" align="center"/> on the toolbar.</p>
        </info>
        <stepresult>
          <p>The <keyword>Insert External Xref Dialog</keyword> will appear.</p>
          <fig>
            <title>Insert External Xref Dialog.</title>
            <image href="insert-external-xref-dialog.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Specify the target file.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>In the <uicontrol>Insert External Xref Dialog</uicontrol>, specify the target file one of these ways:</p>
        </info>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Select an existing file.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>From the <uicontrol>Files</uicontrol> list, select a file.</p>
              <p><image href="insert-external-xreference-dialog.png" align="center" placement="break"/></p>
              <p><note>
                  <p>To filter the files by type, select a type from the <uicontrol>File type</uicontrol> drop-down list.</p>
                </note></p>
            </info>
          </substep>
          <substep id="step-about-link-path">
            <cmd>Enter the path to an existing file or URL manually.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p><ol>
                  <li>
                    <p>In the <uicontrol>Path</uicontrol> field,  type the path to the target file or URL .</p>
                    <image href="path-entered-manually.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
                    <p><note>
                        <p>URLs must start with &quot;<codeph>http://</codeph>&quot;, e.g. <filepath>http://www.syntext.com</filepath>.</p>
                      </note></p>
                    <p><note>
                        <p>It is also possible to type the reference to anything within a topic, using the following format:  
<codeph>filename.xml#topicid/elementid</codeph>.
</p>
                      </note></p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> to apply the typed path.</p>
                    <image href="path-entered-manually-applied.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
                  </li>
                </ol></p>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Specify the target.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>From the <uicontrol>Targets</uicontrol> list, select the target.</p>
          <image href="insert-external-xref-dialog-target-selected.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          <p><note conref="inserting-local-xref.xml#inserting-local-xref/note-targets"/><image href="show-types-list-external-xref.png" align="center" placement="break"/></p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step id="specify-attributes-xref">
        <cmd>Specify <uicontrol>Attributes</uicontrol> if needed:</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Select a format.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>From the <uicontrol>Format</uicontrol> drop-down list, select one of the following:<ul>
                  <li>
                    <p>dita</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>html</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>pdf</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>ditamap</p>
                  </li>
                </ul></p>
              <note id="note-about-url-format">
                <p>If you&apos;ve typed a URL , e.g. <filepath>http://www.syntext.com</filepath>, and pressed <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>, the <codeph>format</codeph> attribute automatically gets the value <codeph>html</codeph>.</p>
              </note>
            </info>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Select a scope.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>From the <uicontrol>Scope</uicontrol> drop-down list, select one of the following:<ul>
                  <li>
                    <p>local</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>peer</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>external</p>
                  </li>
                </ul></p>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Insert</uicontrol> button to insert the external xref.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step conref="inserting-local-xref.xml#inserting-local-xref/step-close-dialog">
        <cmd/>
      </step>
    </steps>
    <result>
      <fig frame="all">
        <title>External xref inserted.</title>
        <image href="external-xref-inserted.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
      </fig>
    </result>
  </taskbody>
</task>
